Today my baby is officially 2 years old. Definitely happy to celebrate all weekend with him and be with family and friends who love him, but man these two years went by way too fast. 

August 25th 2021 at 2:39am my whole world changed in the best way possible. Everything was given new meaning and I felt an overwhelming amount of love that just keeps growing. Getting bigger and stronger by the day just like he is :) I’m excited to see him grow and simultaneously sad to see the smaller versions of him fade away. Bittersweet feelings 🥲 I’ve been told he’s a toddler now and not a baby… agree to disagree! He’ll be the ripe old age of 35 one day and still very much be MY baby. As long as I’m living, my baby you’ll be 💙

Happy birthday to my sweet forever baby boy, Asher 🦖 Love you with everything I’ve got ♥️

Her formal eviction notice has been given. I wasn’t stoked on the idea of induction but she wasn’t moving as much over these last few days. That had me nervous & ready to do this :)

Got here at 6am after cuddling my baby at home one more time. He’s with grandpa today and I’m sure they’ll have fun! Last pregnant pics snapped last night are pretty cute :) 

Still waiting on things to fully progress, but it’s been a pretty chill experience so far. I’ve been here 12hrs but all is good! Mild contractions ramped up and now I have an epidural which is sweet. Just waiting to get to that magical 10 cm (currently 5)! Excited to meet you, baby girl 💗

Welcome to the world, baby Violet 💜 Your mommy, daddy & big brother all love you very much. 

Violet Adriana Frank 
Born 12-21-23 at 8:58PM 🍼 
6lbs 9oz and 20 3/4 in long!

The induction process made labor longer than with Asher, but it was a wonderful experience. Dr broke my water in the morning & shortly followed with Pitocin. Once contractions were bad enough I got my epidural 🙏🏻 and all was easy. Hours later I felt a lot of pressure and asked a nurse to check on me - it was time. 3 easy pushes later and our family went from 3 to 4 💕. I already love her more than any words can say. So very thankful for where life has landed me 🥹

In a single, unforgettable moment, our newborn met her great-grandmother: a century of love passed down in both hello and goodbye. 

I had the opportunity of living with my grandma a few years ago and am forever grateful to know her in such a deep way. Her spirit, so loving, caring, and infectiously happy, has left a lasting mark on me. Every day, I strive to be a bit more like @dorislillianfrank . What a soul. Her memory will be cherished forever. 💔 1923 - 2024
